# Storage boundaries — {{PROJECT_NAME}}

What is stored where, and why. Prevents data leaking into the wrong store (e.g. business
data in preferences, secrets in plain files).

| Store | Holds | Must NOT hold | Key/path convention |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Primary DB | <!-- FILL: source-of-truth entities --> | transient UI state | <!-- FILL --> |
| Key-value / preferences | small flags, settings | business records | <!-- FILL: key naming --> |
| Files / blobs | <!-- FILL --> | <!-- FILL --> | <!-- FILL --> |
| Secure storage | tokens, secrets | anything non-sensitive | <!-- FILL --> |

## Rules
- Persistent business data lives in the primary DB only — never solely in memory/state.
- Storage keys follow the conventions above; adding a key updates this file.
